<div id="divhow" class="infohow">    <h2>How it works</h2>    <div class="howitworks-div">        <div class="howitworks-point">            <span>                <p>                    <span class="number">1</span>                    <img class="howimg" src="./img/howitworks/top100.png">                </p>                 <p>An Open Knowledge Maps visualization presents you with a topical overview for your search term.                    It is based on the 100 <a class="underline" href="./faq">most relevant</a> documents for your search term.                </p>            </span>        </div>        <div class="howitworks-point">            <span>                <p>                    <span class="number">2</span>                    <img class="howimg" src="./img/howitworks/textsimilarity.png">                </p>                <p>We use text similarity to create the knowledge maps.                    The algorithm groups those papers together that have many words in common.                </p>            </span>        </div>        <div class="howitworks-point">            <span>                <p>                    <span class="number">3</span>                    <img class="howimg" src="./img/howitworks/headstart-search.png">                </p>                <p>The visualization is intended to give you a head start on your                     literature search. You can also use Open Knowledge Maps to stay up-to-date -                     just limit your search to the most recent papers in the options.                </p>            </span>        </div>    </div><!--<p style="font-size: 18px; text-align:center;">For more information please <a class="underline" target="_blank" href="http://0277.ch/ojs/index.php/cdrs_0277/article/view/157/355">    read this article</a><br>or     <a class="underline" target="_blank" href="https://github.com/OpenKnowledgeMaps/Headstart/blob/master/server/preprocessing/other-scripts/vis_layout.R">check out the explanation of the code</a> on Github.</p>--></div>